Metadata: Chemistry and revised structure of suvanine

The structure previously proposed for suvanine, a novel tricyclic sesterterpene from the sponge "Ircinia" sp., has been revised, and includes a dimethylguanidi​nium salt of an enol sulfate and an amended ring-junction stereochemistry​. Reexamination of the sponge suggests that it is in the genus "Coscinoderma".
